  "result": "Root cause: `str_packsize` in `crates/lua-stdlib/src/string_lib.rs:2026` used `usize::MAX` as the upper bound for accumulated pack size, so 8 × `c268435456` (= 2,147,483,648 bytes, just over `INT_MAX`) silently returned a giant integer instead of raising `\"format result too large\"`. C-Lua's `MAXSIZE` is `INT_MAX` (not `SIZE_MAX`) on every platform where `size_t >= int`.\n\nFix: added module-level `PACK_MAXSIZE: usize = i32::MAX as usize` mirroring C's `MAXSIZE` macro (`lstrlib.c:49-50`), and changed `str_packsize` to compare against `PACK_MAXSIZE - space` instead of `usize::MAX - space`. Each per-option `space` is bounded well below `PACK_MAXSIZE` by `getnum`'s `(i32::MAX-9)/10` cap, so the subtraction can't underflow.\n\nNew state: verified end-to-end via a probe at `/tmp/tpack_probe.lua` that reproduces `tpack.lua` lines 122–163 (the `\"testing invalid formats\"` and overflow blocks); it now prints `done block 1/2/3` and exits OK where it previously failed on `checkerror(\"too large\", packsize, …)`. `cargo build -q -p lua-cli` is clean (only pre-existing warnings). No temporary eprintln was added.",
